quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  43,16,"What! has He taken to Himself daughters out of all that He creates, and \"honored\" you with sons"
  43,17,"When any of them is given the news of the birth of what he accepts as appropriate for the All-Merciful, his face darkens, choking with anger"
  43,18,"What! (Am I to have a daughter –) one who is brought up in adornments, and unable to be clear in disputation"
  43,19,"And yet they have judged the angels, who are themselves the servants of the All-Merciful, to be females (whom they judge to be of little value, and yet regard as His daughters). Did they witness their creation? This testimony of theirs will be recorded, and they will be called to account (for this falsehood in the Hereafter)"
  43,20,"They also say: \"If the All-Merciful had so willed, we would not have worshipped them (our deities, including angels).\" They have no knowledge whatever of that (the relationship of Divine Will and human will and actions). Indeed, they only judge and speak according to their own fancies and interests"
  43,21,Or did We give them a Book before this (Qur’an) and so they are holding fast to it (and worshipping their false deities by its authority)
  43,22,"Not at all! (Indeed, their only argument is that) they say: \"We have found our forefathers following a certain religion, and we are led in their footsteps"
  43,23,"In just that way, We never sent a warner to a township before you but those of its people who had been lost in the pursuit of pleasures without scruples reacted, saying: \"We have found our forefathers following a religion, and we certainly follow in their footsteps"
  43,24,"He (who was sent to warn them) said: \"What! even though I have come to you with better guidance than what you have found your forefathers following?\" They said: \"Surely we are unbelievers in that with which you have been sent"
  43,25,"So then We took Our retribution on them. So look: how was the outcome for those who denied (God’s Messengers)"